'''H<U+00F6>llriegl, Hellriegel''' is surname of:

* {{link|de|Richard Arnold Bermann}}<ref>aka [[Richard A. Bermann]]</ref>, better known as ''"[[Arnold H<U+00F6>llriegel]]"'' (1883, Vienna - 1939, [[Saratoga Springs]], New York), a Jewish Austrian journalist and travel writer
* {{link|de|Eduard H<U+00F6>llrigl}} (1861 <U+2013> 1901), Austrian book seller and its shopname (fully ''Eduard H<U+00F6>llrigl, vorm. Herm. Kerber'', f. 1598; other hitoric names: ''Konrad K<U+00FC>rner's Hof-Buchdrucker'', ''Herm(ann). Kerber'', etc.); bought the bookstore on 1900; The eldest bookstore of the still today existing bookstores in Austria, and 3rd-eldest in the South German-Austrian area<ref>http://www.salzburg.com/wiki/index.php/Buchhandlung_H%C3%B6llrigl</ref>

== Hellriegel ==
* [[Hans-J<U+00FC>rgen Hellriegel]] (1917, Wilmersdorf, Berlin <U+2013> 1944), [[Kapit<U+00E4>nleutnant]] with the [[Kriegsmarine]] during World War II. 
* {{link|de|Hermann Hellriegel}} (1831, [[Mausitz]] bei [[Pegau]] - 1895), German [[agricultural chemist]]
* [[Jan Hellriegel|Janette "Jan" Hellriegel]] (born ?, [[Waitakere]], Auckland, New Zealand), singer/songwriter based in Auckland, New Zealand
* {{link|de|Ludwig Hellriegel}} (born 1932, [[Bensheim]], Hesse), German Catholic priest and [[church historian]]
* [[Thomas Hellriegel]] (born 1971, [[B<U+00FC>chenau]]), German [[Ironman Triathlon|Ironman triathlete]]

